The son of Royal Media Services mogul S K Macharia was charged before a Nairobi traffic court after failing to follow a traffic officer's order to blow into a breathalyser.John Macharia was accused of failing to follow the directions of a traffic officer on Saturday.John had been in an accident on Waiyaki Way after his Porsche, registration number KCH 929K, rammed into another vehicle.It is believed he was driving under the influence.He pleaded guilty through his lawyer Ian Maina.Maina said his client was remorseful for his actions and did would not repeat the offence.Senior resident magistrate Electra Rianyi issued him with a fine of Sh25,000.